&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Status&lt;/strong&gt; changed from &lt;i&gt;public comment&lt;/i&gt; to &lt;i&gt;author action&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assignee&lt;/strong&gt; changed from &lt;i&gt;Greg Newby&lt;/i&gt; to &lt;i&gt;Jens Jensen&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Dear authors/editors: The tracker wasn't updated yet, to reflect current status, so I am doing this now.&lt;/p&gt;


	&lt;p&gt;My understanding from today's standards council telecon is that all comments were provided by email in October/November 2019, and that the working group has had a phone call to discuss next steps.&lt;/p&gt;


	&lt;p&gt;These next steps, basically, are for the WG to submit a final document that incorporates needed changes due to public comment (including the late-arriving comments mentioned above).&lt;/p&gt;


	&lt;p&gt;Please feel free to check with me, or with Jens (who is acting as your Area Director for this purpose), as needed.&lt;/p&gt;


	&lt;p&gt;Thanks. Greg&lt;/p&gt;    </content>
